Here's how to implement all three in your `EditProductPage`:

**1 & 2. Intercept back navigation and confirm:**

Override `OnBackButtonPressed` (hardware/gesture back) and hook into Shell's `NavigatedFrom`:

```csharp
public partial class EditProductPage : ContentPage
{
    private bool _hasUnsavedChanges;

    protected override bool OnBackButtonPressed()
    {
        if (_hasUnsavedChanges)
        {
            ShowUnsavedChangesDialog();
            return true; // cancel navigation
        }
        return base.OnBackButtonPressed();
    }

    private async void ShowUnsavedChangesDialog()
    {
        bool leave = await DisplayAlert(
            "Unsaved Changes",
            "You have unsaved changes. Discard and go back?",
            "Discard", "Stay");

        if (leave)
        {
            _hasUnsavedChanges = false;
            await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("..");
        }
    }
}
```

**3. Custom "Cancel" back button:**

In your XAML, hide the default back button and add your own toolbar item:

```xml
<ContentPage
    xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
    xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
    x:Class="MyApp.EditProductPage"
    Title="Edit Product"
    Shell.BackButtonBehavior="{StaticResource CancelBackButton}">

    <ContentPage.Resources>
        <BackButtonBehavior
            x:Key="CancelBackButton"
            TextOverride="Cancel"
            Command="{Binding BackCommand}" />
    </ContentPage.Resources>

    <!-- page content -->
</ContentPage>
```

Or set it inline:

```xml
<Shell.BackButtonBehavior>
    <BackButtonBehavior
        TextOverride="Cancel"
        IconOverride=""
        Command="{Binding BackCommand}" />
</Shell.BackButtonBehavior>
```

Wire up `BackCommand` in your view model (or code-behind):

```csharp
public ICommand BackCommand { get; }

public EditProductPage()
{
    InitializeComponent();

    BackCommand = new Command(async () =>
    {
        if (_hasUnsavedChanges)
            ShowUnsavedChangesDialog();
        else
            await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("..");
    });

    BindingContext = this;
}
```

**Key points:**
- `OnBackButtonPressed` handles Android hardware/swipe back — return `true` to cancel.
- `BackButtonBehavior.Command` replaces the Shell toolbar back button tap — it won't navigate unless you explicitly call `GoToAsync("..")`.
- `TextOverride="Cancel"` replaces the arrow with text. Set `IconOverride=""` to suppress the default icon on iOS.
